<div class="hello">
  <h2>HOW TO MAKE PASTA ALLA CARBONARA LIKE A PRO</h2>
</div>

<p>
  To prepare spaghetti alla carbonara, start by placing a pot of salted water on the stove to cook the pasta. Meanwhile, remove the rind from the guanciale and cut it first into slices (1) and then into strips about 1cm thick (2, 3). The leftover rind can be reused to flavor other dishes.
</p>

<div class="recipe-section">
  <img src="https://ricette.giallozafferano.it/images/ricette/244/24489/24489_draft-spaghetti-alla-carbonara_strip_1-3.jpg" alt="Carbonara preparation steps 1-3">
  <p>Pour the pieces of guanciale into a non-stick pan (4) and sauté for about 10 minutes over medium-high heat, being careful not to burn it, as this would release too strong a flavor. Meanwhile, drop the spaghetti into the boiling water (5) and cook them al dente. In the meantime, pour the egg yolks into a bowl (6).</p>
  <img src="https://ricette.giallozafferano.it/images/ricette/244/24489/24489_draft-spaghetti-alla-carbonara_strip_4-6.jpg" alt="Carbonara preparation steps 4-6">
  <p>Add the Pecorino (7) and season with black pepper (8). Whisk everything together by hand (9) until you obtain a smooth cream.</p>
  <img src="https://ricette.giallozafferano.it/images/ricette/244/24489/24489_draft-spaghetti-alla-carbonara_strip_7-9.jpg" alt="Carbonara preparation steps 7-9">
 <p>Meanwhile, the guanciale will be cooked (10); turn off the heat and, using a ladle, remove it from the pan, leaving the cooking juices in the pan (11). Transfer the guanciale to a small bowl and set it aside. Pour a ladle of pasta water into the pan (12), along with the guanciale fat.</p>
   <img src="https://ricette.giallozafferano.it/images/ricette/244/24489/24489_draft-spaghetti-alla-carbonara_strip_10-12.jpg" alt="Carbonara preparation steps 10-12">
</div>

